<td style="text-align: right"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Philosophy" title="Portal:Philosophy">Philosophy Portal</a></b> ·&#160;<span class="noprint plainlinksneverexpand navbar" style="background:none; padding:0; font-weight:normal;; font-size:xx-small;"><a href="/wiki/Template:Humanism" title="Template:Humanism"><span title="View this template" style="">v</span></a>&#160;<span style="font-size:80%;">•</span>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Template_talk:Humanism" title="Template talk:Humanism"><span title="Discussion about this template" style="">d</span></a>&#160;<span style="font-size:80%;">•</span>&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Humanism&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Humanism&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow"><span title="Edit this template" style=";">e</span></a></span>&#160;</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Secular humanism</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Humanism" title="Humanism">humanist</a> philosophy that upholds <a href="/wiki/Reason" title="Reason">reason</a>, <a href="/wiki/Ethics" title="Ethics">ethics</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Justice" title="Justice">justice</a>, and specifically rejects the <a href="/wiki/Supernatural" title="Supernatural">supernatural</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Spirituality" title="Spirituality">spiritual</a> as the basis of moral reflection and decision-making. Like other types of humanism, secular humanism is a <a href="/wiki/Life_stance" title="Life stance">life stance</a> that focuses on the way human beings can lead good, happy and functional lives.</p>
<p>The term "secular humanism" was coined in the 20th century to make a clear distinction from "<a href="/wiki/Religious_humanism" title="Religious humanism">religious humanism</a>". A related concept is "scientific humanism", which biologist <a href="/wiki/Edward_O._Wilson" title="Edward O. Wilson" class="mw-redirect">Edward O. Wilson</a> claimed to be "the only worldview compatible with <a href="/wiki/Science" title="Science">science's</a> growing knowledge of the real world and the laws of nature".<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
