<li><a href="/wiki/Friedrich_Engels" title="Friedrich Engels">Friedrich Engels</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Scott_Fellows" title="Scott Fellows">Scott Fellows</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/E._M._Forster" title="E. M. Forster">E. M. Forster</a> (see in particular his "<a href="/wiki/What_I_Believe" title="What I Believe">What I Believe</a>")</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Hubert_Harrison" title="Hubert Harrison">Hubert Harrison</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Butch_Hartman" title="Butch Hartman">Butch Hartman</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Andreas_Heldal-Lund" title="Andreas Heldal-Lund">Andreas Heldal-Lund</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Nat_Hentoff" title="Nat Hentoff">Nat Hentoff</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Julian_Huxley" title="Julian Huxley">Julian Huxley</a> - first President of the <a href="/wiki/IHEU" title="IHEU" class="mw-redirect">IHEU</a>, a major <a href="/wiki/Humanism_(life_stance)" title="Humanism (life stance)">Humanist</a> organisation</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Paul_Kurtz" title="Paul Kurtz">Paul Kurtz</a> - founding President of the <a href="/wiki/Council_for_Secular_Humanism" title="Council for Secular Humanism">Council for Secular Humanism</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Corliss_Lamont" title="Corliss Lamont">Corliss Lamont</a> <a href="http://www.corliss-lamont.org/" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.corliss-lamont.org/" rel="nofollow">[2]</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/John_Lennon" title="John Lennon">John Lennon</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Taslima_Nasrin" title="Taslima Nasrin">Taslima Nasrin</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Linus_Pauling" title="Linus Pauling">Linus Pauling</a></li>
